properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 13 at 3:30AM MST until January 14 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH.

* WHERE...Interstate 25 near Bordeaux between Chugwater and
Wheatland.

* WHEN...From 2 PM this afternoon to 11 AM MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will
create dangerous travel conditions and a high blow over risk for
light and high profile vehicles, including camping and tractor
trailers.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 11 AM MST TUESDAY
